            <p>Glen Ridge. N.Y. 26<hi rend="sup">th</hi> June&#47;84<lb/></p>
                
            <p>Dear Sir&#44;<lb/></p>
            <p>I sent you  the <emph rend="italics">Shophar</emph><lb/> last week&#44; on approval&#44; but had<lb/> no time to write you ere this&#44; which I<lb/> regret. Having promised the owner<lb/>a reply the early part of this week&#44;<lb/> I would be glad to learn whether it<lb/> has proved suitable. Otherwise please<lb/> return it to 35 Broadway&#44; New York.<lb/> It was sent you by Adams Express<lb/> and I trust reached you in due course.<lb/> When I have more time shall do my&#45;<lb/>self the pleasure of writing you more<lb/> lengthily in answer to your esteemed<lb/> lines of 13<hi rend="sup">th</hi> Inst.<lb/></p>
            <p>Yours truly<lb/>
                David M. P&#239;za<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev. S. Morais&#44; Phila.<lb/></p>
        </body>
